node.text:
Follow @dr.raymondgardinier for scientifically proven and evidence based nutrition, mindset, and fitness tips!

Who got in phenomenal shape after just one workout?

Or after eating just one salad?

Or going without one dessert?

No one.

So the “unsexy” secret to success is - your results come from your daily habits.

This is why most programs and diets fail.

Fad diets and extreme workout programs aren’t something most people can stick to for more than a few weeks or months at a time.

So the real question then isn’t “what works?” 

It’s “What works day after day, year after year?”

The answer is whatever you can stick to for the long haul.

Simplicity and convenience is key when it comes to getting consistent with nutrition and fitness.

And when you’re consistent, you don’t have to give up your favorite foods or spend countless hours exercising.

Because that’s just not sustainable.

My go-to smoothie:
1 cup frozen blueberries
1/2 banana
1 scoop creatine
2 scoops protein (not 1)
1.5 cup almond milk
1 tsp cinnamon

Full recipe below, send it to a friend who’d love this!⁣
By: Robin Broadfoot and Tasty

Ingredients (for 8 servings)
VEGGIES
2 eggplants
6 roma tomatoes
2 yellow squashes
2 zucchinis
SAUCE
2 tablespoons olive oil
1 onion, diced
4 cloves garlic, minced
1 red bell pepper, diced
1 yellow bell pepper, diced
salt, to taste
pepper, to taste
28 oz can of crushed tomatoes (795 g)
2 tablespoons chopped fresh basil, from 8-10 leaves
HERB SEASONING
2 tablespoons chopped fresh basil, from 8-10 leaves
1 teaspoon garlic, minced
2 tablespoons Chopped fresh parsley
2 teaspoons fresh thyme
salt, to taste
pepper, to taste
4 tablespoons olive oil

Preparation
Preheat the oven for 375˚F (190˚C).
Slice the eggplant, tomatoes, squash, and zucchini into approximately ¹⁄₁₆-inch (1-mm) rounds, then set aside.
Make the sauce: Heat the olive oil in a 12-inch (30-cm) oven-safe pan over medium-high heat. Sauté the onion, garlic, and bell peppers until soft, about 10 minutes. Season with salt and pepper, then add the crushed tomatoes. Stir until the ingredients are fully incorporated. Remove from heat, then add the basil. Stir once more, then smooth the surface of the sauce with a spatula.
Arrange the sliced veggies in alternating patterns, (for example, eggplant, tomato, squash, zucchini) on top of the sauce from the outer edge to the middle of the pan. Season with salt and pepper. Cover the pan with foil and bake for 40 minutes. Uncover, then bake for another 20 minutes, until the vegetables are softened.
Mix herb seasoning ingredients and pour over the cooked ratatouille.
Serve while hot as a main dish or side. The ratatouille is also excellent the next day--cover with foil and reheat in a 350˚F (180˚C) oven for 15 minutes, or simply microwave to desired temperature.
Enjoy!
---

🍗 A very simple, easy and delicious way to enjoy regular chicken breast! 🙃😍⁣
⁣
These boneless skinless chicken breasts are covered in a light and flavorful herby marinade, with garlic, fresh cilantro, and lime. Grilled to perfection, perfect for the coming summer...By @healthyfitnessmeals⁣
⁣
Cilantro Lime Chicken 🌱 🍗⁣
📝 Ingredients⁣
* 8 Boneless skinless chicken breasts about 2 lbs.⁣
* Marinade:⁣
* 2/3 bunch fresh cilantro⁣
* zest of 1 lime⁣
* 3 Tbsp lime juice about 2 limes⁣
* 3 cloves garlic chopped⁣
* 1 tsp ground coriander⁣
* 1 tsp salt⁣
* 1 tsp black pepper⁣
* 2 tbsp olive oil⁣
* Optional Garnishes:⁣
* Cilantro leaves⁣
* Lime wedges⁣
.⁣
👩‍🍳 Instructions⁣
1. Combine all the marinade ingredients to a blender or food processor and pulse until it forms a smooth mixture.⁣
⁣
2. Add chicken breast to a large freezer-safe sealable bag, followed by the marinade. Press the air out of the bag and seal it tightly. Now gently press to the marinade around the chicken cutlets to coat well.⁣
⁣
3. Allow it to marinate in the refrigerator for at least 1 hour to overnight. Marinating overnight will enhance the juiciness and flavor of the chicken.⁣
⁣
4. Next, brush the grill or a heavy-bottomed pan with some oil and heat over medium-high heat. Place the marinated chicken breast onto the hot grill.⁣
⁣
5. Grill without moving them around, about 5 minutes on each side, or until charred and cooked through.⁣
⁣
6. Garnish with fresh cilantro leaves and serve with lime wedges if desired.⁣
⁣

Cut the potatoes in fourths and toss them in oil and all the seasoning. Baked in my convection oven at 425 for 15 minutes.⁣

🥑Follow @Dr.Stefan.Gospodinov for the most SUSTAINABLE health, nutrition, and fitness tips!⁣
-⁣
⚠️ Read the CAPTION 👇 by @lucymountain⁣
my explore page: can you do this 4 week challenge???⁠⠀⁣
me, very loudly inside my head: no⁠⠀⁣
.⁣
I used to bloody love an Instagram fitness challenge. For a very vivid period of my life, nothing would quite excite me like a good old squat challenge infographic with a diagram of someone’s arse.⁠⠀⁣
⁠⠀⁣
And Sundays too. I loved Sundays.⁠⠀⁣
⁠⠀⁣
Those were the days I’d make a mental note for the week - identifying all the beige and circular foods I was going to cut out my diet STARTING TOMORROW.⁠ Biscuits, burgers, bagels, bread. Basically anything beige.⁠⠀⁣
⁠⠀⁣
All under the guise of #health, of course.⁠⠀⁣
I felt good, I felt virtuous.⁠⠀⁣
⁠⠀⁣
However my efforts had a solid 0% success rating. Why? Because I liked biscuits. And burgers. And bagels. And bread.⁠⠀⁣
⁠⠀⁣
Ironically, attempting to cut them out my life actually increased the amount of mental energy I spent thinking about them by about 300%. Funny that.⁠⠀⁣
⁠⠀⁣
And no. Don’t panic.⁠⠀⁣
This isn’t going to be post telling you to JuSt eAt WHaT yOu WanT.⁠⠀⁣
Because a diet consisting of *only* those foods probably ain’t going to make you happy, healthy human. And it’s okay to have goals.⁠⠀⁣
⁠⠀⁣
But ! ! !⁠⠀⁣
⁠⠀⁣
The thing I always seemed to forget was that eating a balanced diet requires me to make room for *all* foods I enjoy. Nutritious things and less so.⁠⠀⁣
Trying to do anything but that was just stalling time - valuable time which I could have spent teaching myself moderation. And how to stop demonising round, doughy foods beginning B.⁠⠀⁣
⁠⠀⁣
Or having a meltdown in the presence of Sandra’s bloody party tray bake 5 days in. God love her.⁠⠀⁣
⁠⠀⁣
A 4 week challenge to eat more vegetables, drink more water and do more steps isn’t as sexy nor would it warrant BIG RED CROSSES or a clipart of a sixpack but I’d argue it’d be 4 weeks better spent.⁠⠀⁣
⁣
